Samsung has revealed its latest tablet, the 10-inch Galaxy Tab S5e. The tablet runs Android 9 and is Samsung’s thinnest and lightest tablet, weighing 400g and measuring 5.1mm thick. It offers owners a 64-bit octa-core processor, a 13MP rear camera and an 8MP front camera, and will feature Bixby 2.0. The Tab S5e also features a Super AMOLED 16:10 display, as well as quad speakers and Dolby Atmos integration for “immersive 3D sound and professionally balanced audio”. “The Tab S5e is a top-tier tablet with a sleek design and powerful features, available at a new price point,” said Samsung. The Tab S5e will begin at $399, and will release in the second quarter of 2019.   